cdata.name: Authoreon
cdata.desc:
Authoreon is a platform designed to verify personal and professional data. It has created two additional separate overlay protocols on top of the blockchain: the synapse and the access lock layers. This 3-layer architecture secures ownership and decentralizes authorization through use-case-specific smart contracts in combination with the interplanetary database (IPDB) and the interplanetary file system (IPFS). 

The Authoreon (AUN) token is an Ethereum-based (ERC-20) cryptocurrency. It is the token that fuels the platform as it is used to access the available services and goods.
